<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-10-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-10-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="435" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d435">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Provisional Governor of
                            Cuba</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-10-06"><hi rend="italic">October 6,
                                1906</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inclose for your
                            information copy of a note from Mr. Quesada, the Cuban minister at this
                            capital, expressing his confidence in the right intentions of the
                            American Government and people in the matter of their intervention in
                            Cuba, and stating that he will remain at his post while he can serve
                            Cuba and aid in promoting relations of confidence and trust between the
                            two Governments.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">E. Root.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>